President Biden delivered remarks in the East Room of the White House, highlighting the nominations of two women for four-star command positions in the Armed Forces. He nominated General Jacqueline Van Ovost as Commander of the United States Transportation Command and Lieutenant General Laura Richardson as Commander in the United States Southern Command. If confirmed, they will become the second and third women in history to lead combatant commands. President Biden emphasized the importance of recognizing and celebrating the accomplishments of these women and the doors they have opened for future generations. He also discussed the need for continued progress in creating a more inclusive and equitable military, addressing issues such as gender equality, diversity in leadership, and combating sexual assault. The President expressed his commitment to working towards these goals and ensuring the safety and success of all service members.